In the story, The Tortoise and The Hare, a slight rivalry begins between a hare a tortoise. Therefore, The Hare, who wants to prove
himself, asks the tortoise for a race from one side of the island to another. The Tortoise, without any objection agrees. Soon after
the agreement, the race begins. The Hare hops and runs very fast and reaches half-way of the race very quickly. Meanwhile, the tortoise
continues in its steady slow motion. The Hare thinking that he is way ahead of the tortoise takes a nap under a tree and sleeps for
a long time. After a long while, the Hare still sleeping, the Tortoise reaches the Hare. The Tortoise continues it race without a sound. 